<https://w3id.org/pink#attributed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Relates an agent to an entity via an activity that both the agent and entity participates to."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#attributed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "attributed"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#attributed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "The activity is through overlapped by the agent and overcrossed by the entity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#attributed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "There may or may not be a causal interaction between the agent and entity."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInfluencedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A relation between an entity that causally affects the subject."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "John yesterday is the cause of John today, is an example of temporal-like causality. The desk supporting my laptop is a space-like causality."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#causedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "causedBy"@en .
