# 
# https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/hasPart> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/pink#overlaps> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ReflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/pink#isOvercrossedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The primitive relation that express the concept of an entity being part of another one."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "hasPart"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "OWL2 does not allow non-simple (e.g. transitive) properties to appear in disjoint property axioms. We therefore implement the transitivity of hasPart using SWRL rules instead of asserting it with owl:TransitiveProperty."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pink#hasParticipant
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasParticipant> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
