<https://w3id.org/pink#hasTemporalPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasTemporalPart> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasTemporalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A relation that identify a proper item part of the whole, whose parts always cover the full spatial extension of the whole within a time interval." .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasTemporalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "hasTemporalPart"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasTemporalPart> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "A temporal part of an item cannot both cause and be caused by any other proper part of the item."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/pink#hasDescription> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/pink#Property> .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://purl.org/vocab/vann/usageNote> "A universal restriction should be used when referring to a unit in EMMO.  For example:\n\n    :LethalDose50\n        a pink:Toxicity , [\n            a owl:Restriction ;\n            owl:onProperty pink:hasUnit ;\n            owl:someValuesFrom emmo:MilliGramPerKiloGram\n        ] .\n"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Connects a property to its unit."@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "hasUnit"@en .
<https://w3id.org/pink#hasUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote> "`pink:hasUnit` is intended to refer to a unit in an existing unit ontology, like QUDT or EMMO."@en .
